In this folder "page" there is 3 main html files general_logistics.html, lectures.html, syllabus.html

**Important: Do not work directly on the master branch.**

Before making any changes, please create and checkout a new branch:

```sh
git checkout -b your-feature-branch
```

Replace `your-feature-branch` with a descriptive name for your work. Always submit changes via a pull request to master.

general_logistics includes:

TA list
Lectures Calendar
OH calendar


syllabus.html includes:

Syllabus


lectures.html includes:

Lectures table
Assignments table
Recitations and Hackathon tables
NOTE: these tables are generated by generate_table.py with the content taken from tables_data folder and the templates taken from tables_templates. The final output is then stored at tables folder which lectures.html file uses to render the tables.


# Setting up the Python Environment with Miniconda

## 1. Install Miniconda (if not already installed)


You can download the Miniconda installer for your operating system from the official website:

https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html

Follow the instructions on the website to install Miniconda for macOS, Linux, or Windows. After installation, restart your terminal or run:

```sh
source ~/miniconda3/bin/activate
```

## 2. Create and activate a conda environment


```sh
conda create -n idls_website python=3.10
conda activate idls_website
```

## 3. Install required Python packages

```sh
conda install pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## 4. Generate the tables

```sh
python generate_table.py
```